.TH "__round_jiffies_up_relative" 9 "__round_jiffies_up_relative" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__round_jiffies_up_relative \- function to round jiffies up to a full second
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" __round_jiffies_up_relative
.BI "(unsigned long j "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "j" 12
the time in (relative) jiffies that should be rounded
.IP "cpu" 12
the processor number on which the timeout will happen
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the same as \fB__round_jiffies_relative\fP except that it will never
round down.  This is useful for timeouts for which the exact time
of firing does not matter too much, as long as they don't fire too
early.
